          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the caster sugar, oil, eggs, and vanilla until combined. Stir in the melted chocolate. Sift in the cocoa, flour, baking powder, and salt and fold until a sticky dough forms. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours until firm enough to handle.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Line two baking trays with baking paper. Sift the icing sugar into a shallow bowl. Roll the cold dough into balls of about 25 g each. Roll each ball generously in icing sugar until completely coated, be thorough, as thin spots will not crack attractively. Place on the lined trays 5 cm apart. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until the surface has cracked and the edges are set but the centre still looks slightly underdone. The cookies firm up as they cool. Leave on the tray for 5 minutes before transferring to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
